{
  "stem": "322.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there were quite a number who actually ate themselves to death.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They couldn't digest that rich food they were cooking right after we were liberated.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The liberators were the Americans, yes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was there, of course.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As I said, I was there in April, the whole month of April, then May, June, finally left in July.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But almost three and a half to four months, I was recuperating.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And to tell you, frankly, all that time that I was recuperating, somehow I sensed and I feared [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that this is not liberation for me, that what I'm going to find out is going to be devastating for me.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And perhaps it's better that I should have not been liberated.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because I felt that-- I already knew that I had no father.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "At Buchenwald, I found out from someone who was with my father in Jaworzno, in a subcamp of Auschwitz, in the coal mines.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In fact, it was Friedman, the one that he worked for.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He told me that your father, oy vey.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I says, what do you mean, oy vey?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then he explained to me later, you know, that he died.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He died the last day of Hanukkah, which was December [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] 1944.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He just gave up, apparently.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "His body was dragged out of the bunk.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then my brother, when the evacuation took place, he either refused to go-- and they took those who did not want to leave out to the woods and shot them.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And somehow, I suspected.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because I saw my mother.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
